  "plan": "Replace `/app/steal.py` with a more robust pipeline: sample many random lines, detect kinks using directional second differences, refine each kink by bisecting the directional derivative, compute full-gradient jumps on both sides with multi-step averaging, reject contaminated jumps by checking multiple offset pairs, cluster normalized jump vectors by strict cosine similarity, and keep the 20 most frequent directions. Then run it and verify against true `A1` using cosine similarity and linear-sum assignment.",
